          >
            {#each [0, 1] as dot, i}
              <button
                class="carousel-dot {currentSlide1 === i ? 'active' : ''}"
                onclick={() => scrollToSlide1(i)}
                aria-label="Go to image {i + 1}"
              ></button>
            {/each}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="page-text mt-[30px]">
      Built with Next.js and React, the site leverages server-side rendering and
      static generation for performance and SEO. Tailwind CSS powers a
      consistent, utility-first design system, complemented by lightweight CSS
      animations and Next.js image optimization. The codebase follows a modular,
      data-driven structure that is easy to extend and maintain, with standard
      Node.js tooling (npm/yarn) and an MIT license supporting open
      collaboration and deployment.
    </p>
